HEADWORD: Quindecylic
<hw>Quin`de*cyl"ic</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>quindecim</ets> fifteen + <ets>-yl</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Chem.)</fld>
<def>Pertaining to, or designating, an acid of the fatty acid series,
containing fifteen atoms of carbon; called also
<altname>pentadecylic</altname> acid.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

